result.execSummary:
The defendant Frankie James Torres was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • False Imprisonment [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).
  • Child Abuse-Recklessly Cause Harm, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(3)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Frankie James Torres in court with attorney Michael Hart.  Defendant Frankie James Torres in custody.  Matthew James Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Sentencing hearing continued.   Statements by defense counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 473 days served.  Court ordered 2 YEARS Initial Term Of Confinement and 2 YEARS Extended Supervision.

AS TO COUNT 2:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 0 days served.  Court ordered 2 YEARS Initial Term Of Confinement and 2 YEARS Extended Supervision.

AS TO COUNT 4:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 3 YEARS 6 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prison, concurrent with any other sentence; credit for 473 days served.  Court ordered 1 YEAR 6 MONTHS Initial Term Of Confinement and 2 YEARS Extended Supervision.

AS TO COUNT 5:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 2 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 0 days served.  Court ordered 1 YEAR Initial Term Of Confinement and 1 YEAR Extended Supervision.

Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- No further violations of the law.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- Court referred Defendant to the Mental Health Unit for mental health evaluation; take all prescribed medications.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random screens.
- No possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.
- Phone and mail contact with victim is allowed, however; no other contact with victim during the entire sentence unless approved by agent.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and supervision fees.
   The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
